Analysis of the Main Target Image

• Block Count and Layers  
  – There are 9 total blocks arranged in 3 layers.  
    1) Bottom Layer (3 blocks)  
       – A red arch‐block in the center, flanked by two yellow cubes (left and right).  
    2) Second Layer (4 blocks)  
       – A green cube and a blue cube side‐by‐side on top of the arch.  
       – An orange wedge on top of each yellow cube (left and right “shoulders”).  
    3) Top Layer (2 blocks)  
       – Two orange wedges meeting at the peak to form the “roof.”  

• Spatial Relationships  
  – Bottom layer forms a straight row: [Yellow cube | Red arch | Yellow cube].  
  – Second layer sits atop the bottom:  
     • Green cube and blue cube directly above the arch (center).  
     • Orange wedges rest above the yellow cubes, each sloping inward.  
  – Top layer has two orange wedges forming a triangular “roof” over the cubes.  

Selection of Required Blocks from the Dictionary

1. Red Arch (hole front‐to‐back): Block #1  
2. Blue Cube: Block #6  
3. Green Cube: Block #7  
4. Yellow Cube (used twice): Block #9  
5. Orange Wedges (four distinct orientations needed):  
   • Second‐layer left wedge: Block #15  
   • Second‐layer right wedge: Block #16  
   • Top‐layer left wedge: Block #13  
   • Top‐layer right wedge: Block #14  

Note that no rotations other than those shown in the dictionary are permitted. The above choices match color, shape, and orientation exactly as in the target image.

Assembly Instructions

{  
  Step1: Move block with index 9    // Bottom‐left yellow cube  
  Step2: Move block with index 1    // Red arch block in the middle  
  Step3: Move block with index 9    // Bottom‐right yellow cube  
  Step4: Move block with index 15   // Left orange wedge on top of left cube  
  Step5: Move block with index 7    // Green cube above arch (left center)  
  Step6: Move block with index 6    // Blue cube above arch (right center)  
  Step7: Move block with index 16   // Right orange wedge on top of right cube  
  Step8: Move block with index 13   // Top‐layer left orange wedge  
  Step9: Move block with index 14   // Top‐layer right orange wedge  
}
